videos.description: Lucas N'Guessan dunks off the assist from Jawun Evans.
videos.headline: Oklahoma State starts scoring with dunk

videos.description: West Virginia's Esa Ahmad blocks the lay-in attempt from Oklahoma State's Phil Forte III.
videos.headline: WVU's Ahmad gets chase-down block

videos.description: West Virginia's Nathan Adrian blocks Oklahoma State's Jeffrey Carroll, Adrian with the outlet pass to Daxter Miles Jr. who draws the foul for And-1 opportunity.
videos.headline: WVU turns a block into And-1

videos.description: Oklahoma State's Cameron McGriff makes the circus layup, draws the foul for the And-1 opportunity.
videos.headline: OKST makes the acrobatic lay-in and gets the foul

videos.description: West Virginia's Jevon Carter hits the 3-Pointer after Lamont West keeps the ball in bounds on the save.
videos.headline: WVU somehow keeps the ball in play and hits the 3

videos.description: Oklahoma State's Jeffrey Carroll makes the contested layup with West Virginia's Esa Ahmad getting called with the foul.
videos.headline: Oklahoma State makes the contested lay-in for and-1

videos.description: West Virginia's Daxter Miles Jr. gets a steal, and the Mountaineers great ball movement leads to an and-1 opportunity by Teyvon Myers.
videos.headline: West Virginia's ball movement leads to and-1

videos.description: West Virginia's Brandon Watkins dunks off the great assist from Teyvon Myers.
videos.headline: West Virginia dunks it off great pass

videos.description: West Virginia's Esa Ahmad gets the steal from Oklahoma State's Jawun Evans, and the Mountaineers' Jevon Cater passes it to Ahmad who throws it down for the monster jam.
videos.headline: West Virginia's Ahmad makes the one-handed dunk

videos.description: Breaking down West Virginia's strong press defense against Oklahoma State, as they win 92-75.
videos.headline: Breaking down West Virginia's defense against Oklahoma State
